      "content": "Clarithromycin is a strong antibiotic that can significantly increase the levels of simvastatin in your blood, raising the risk of dangerous muscle damage. You should absolutely stop taking your simvastatin for the duration of the antibiotic course and restart it only after your doctor confirms the infection is fully cleared. Please follow this exact protocol to avoid severe side effects, and do not hesitate to call your provider immediately if you experience any muscle pain or weakness.",
