      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "No, simply spacing them out by a few hours will not prevent clarithromycin from inhibiting the liver enzymes that metabolize simvastatin, so the dangerous buildup will still occur. You must completely stop the simvastatin while on this specific antibiotic, regardless of the time of day you take them. Please follow this strict rule to protect your heart and muscles, and do not try to figure out a workaround without your doctor's explicit approval.",
